  "prompt": "Does using Marijuana for a prolonged period of time increase a persons chances of being diagnosed with schizophrenia?",
  "response": "Research suggests that there may be a connection between prolonged marijuana use and an increased risk of developing schizophrenia, particularly in individuals who are predisposed to the disorder. Studies have indicated that heavy and frequent use of marijuana, especially during adolescence when the brain is still developing, may be associated with a higher risk of psychotic disorders, including schizophrenia.\n\nHowever, it's important to note that the relationship is complex. Not everyone who uses marijuana will develop schizophrenia, and many factors contribute to the risk of developing this condition, including genetic vulnerability, environmental influences, and other psychological factors.\n\nIf you or someone you know is concerned about the risks associated with marijuana use and mental health, it may be helpful to consult with a healthcare professional for personalized advice and support.",
